{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow people receiving State Pension to receive Carer's Allowance",
        "additional_details": "State Retirement Pension is treated as an overlapping benefit and therefore disentitles a person to Carers Allowance. This dates back to the Overlapping Benefit Regulations 1979.\r\n\r\nThis archaic regulation needs to be amended to remove Retirement Pension as an Overlapping Benefit or alternatively provide an amendment to allow Carer's Allowance to be paid irrespective of Retirement Pension.\r\n\r\nUnpaid Carers save billions in social care provision and should not be penalised for caring in the community.",
        "background": "Unpaid Carers receive a Carer's Allowance of \u00a367.60 per week, but when the Carer becomes a State Pensioner, this is taken away from them even if they continue to provide essential care to someone.",
